description:
A university CTO has requested a comprehensive inventory report of all SEB Server configurations ahead of the annual IT security audit. Generate a structured JSON report by querying the SEB Server's MariaDB database (container: 'seb-server-mariadb', database: 'SEBServer', user: 'root', password: 'sebserver123').

The report must include data from the 'institution', 'user', and 'configuration_node' tables. When processing the 'user' table, map the 'role' integer values to their corresponding names: 0 = SEB_SERVER_ADMIN, 1 = INSTITUTIONAL_ADMIN, 2 = EXAM_ADMIN, 4 = EXAM_SUPPORTER.

Save the final report to ~/Documents/seb_inventory_report.json using the following structure:
{
  "report_title": "SEB Server Configuration Inventory",
  "generated_by": "IT Administrator",
  "institutions": [
    {"id": <int>, "name": "<string>", "active": <boolean>}
  ],
  "user_accounts": [
    {"username": "<string>", "name": "<string>", "email": "<string>", "role": "<role_name_string>", "institution_id": <int>, "active": <boolean>}
  ],
  "exam_configurations": [
    {"id": <int>, "name": "<string>", "description": "<string>", "institution_id": <int>, "status": "<string>"}
  ],
  "summary": {
    "total_institutions": <count>,
    "total_users": <count>,
    "total_exam_configurations": <count>
  }
}
All data and summary counts must accurately reflect the current database records.
